text: Is there an ideological narrative that explains this? (Seems like something we need.) ...
... "And then women completely lost their minds" doesn't seem quite theoretically penetrating enough.
It's over less than two decades, though. Pretty sure we had birth control before 2007.
Still Shakespeare (until it ceases to be an English-speaking nation).
... So the spontaneous consensus arising in the comments to this: Lose your religion and women will make terminating your civilization their religion.
Anyone who travels widely and in the process becomes less persuaded of the obvious truths of Human Biological Diversity is literally retarded.

... It's logically impossible to say "Wow, I really like these people" without succumbing to something close to absolute political extremism. (Thais might have pushed me over the edge, and not in a sleazy way.)
... So actually we're not remotely all the same, what then?
Does welfare fraud count as a trade?
This happened in less than (the last) two decades?
Transcendental (ahistorical) insights are not helpful to this.
Mass importation of drastically economically net negative populations is the only solution.
... Absolutely mind-melting that anyone ever fell for this bullshit, let alone that some still do.
Literally swooning at my own innocence right now.

... "... no, I never did, not once, in my entire life."
Easiest passage through the Pearly Gates grilling in human history (so long as I can keep it on topic).
